We recommended Management to submit the following for review and evaluation in compliance to CSC Memorandum Circular No. 1, s. 2001:

Copy of the LGU Program on Awards and Incentives for Service Excellence (PRAISE) or the Employee Suggestions and Incentive Awards System duly approved by the Civil Service Commission for CY 2018 and CY 2019. Such copy of the annual report on the awards and incentives system which should be submitted to; the CSC on or before the 30th day of January;
Agency annual work and financial plan and budget showing that at least 5% of the HRD Funds was allocated for the PRAISE;
Proof showing that the monetary awards shall be granted only when the suggestions, inventions, superior accomplishments and other personal efforts result in monetary savings which shall not exceed 20% of the savings generated; and
Justification/explanation on the procedures in evaluating the nominees and the mechanism for recognizing the awardees.

We recommended to Management the following remedial measures:

1. a.) Create a team to conduct an immediate physical count of all its property, plant and equipment. This committee may be composed of the heads or representatives from the Office of the Municipal Treasurer, the Municipal Accountant, the Municipal Engineer, and a representative from the Office of the Municipal Mayor. They are required to submit the RPCPPE on or before January 31 of each year, copy furnished the COA Auditor concerned pursuant to Section 124 of NGAS Manual, Volume I;

b.)Require each Department Head to conduct every year a physical inventory count of all properties under their office and to submit inventory report to the inventory committee for the random validation of the existence of the property; 

c.) Further, the committee should be required to check the condition of the property. Any damage, obsolete and unserviceable property shall be reported in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report and immediately request for disposal. Lastly, the inventory reports should be reconciled with the accounting records to determine the correctness of the property records;

Additional personnel to assist both the Accountant and Treasurer to prepare and maintain records and ledgers all properties owned by the Municipality; and 

Provide depreciation to all its depreciable assets and adjust the Government Equity for the unaccounted accumulated depreciation of the previous years in order to fairly present the accounts in compliance to Paragraph 27 of PPSAS No.1.

